    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/8",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">If <i>b&lt;w</i>, with <i>b</i> possibly 0, or if <i>b&gt;w</i> with <i>w</i> possibly 0, then this option becomes the best of or worst of option, respectively. On the other hand, if <i>b</i> = <i>w</i>, with equal number of underperforming and outperforming stocks removed, this option becomes, in effect, a \"middle of the road\" or an \"average of averages\" option. By removing the outliers, we are removing extreme risk and lowering the premium, while making it more favorable to risk-averse customers. For example, it can provide protection against defaults for the price of missing out on top performers.</p>",
