    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/10",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">In the simplest of implementations, as in single-name options, the asset price processes are modeled as lognormal processes but with a correlation matrix. In more advanced implementations, to account for the volatility smile, some versions of stochastic volatility models are often used. One may even model some form of default component. However, in these more complex models, the modeling of correlation and its estimation become more complex as well.</p>",
